    "plan_content": "The plan is ready for your review. Here's a quick summary:\n\n**4 files** to create/modify:\n\n1. **`stepper.tsx`** — 7-part compound component using a dual-context pattern (like carousel.tsx): `Stepper`, `StepperItem`, `StepperTrigger`, `StepperTitle`, `StepperDescription`, `StepperSeparator`, `StepperContent`\n2. **`stepper-demo.tsx`** — Interactive 3-step demo (\"Account\" → \"Profile\" → \"Complete\") with Prev/Next buttons\n3. **`ui/_registry.ts`** — Insert entry after \"spinner\" (alphabetical order)\n4. **`examples/_registry.ts`** — Insert entry after \"spinner-item\"\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n- Two React contexts: `StepperContext` (root: activeStep + orientation) and `StepperItemContext` (per-item: step number + computed state)\n- `Stepper` root uses `flex-row flex-wrap` for horizontal mode so `StepperContent` breaks to a new line via `basis-full`\n- `StepperTrigger` shows `step + 1` (1-based display) or a `CheckIcon` when completed\n- `StepperSeparator` fills with `bg-primary` when its parent item is completed — standard stepper UX\n- Zero new dependencies (only `lucide-react` which is already project-wide)",
